tool_description: Meme Generator with support of adding captions and text directly on images to over 1.8k meme templates in 10+ fonts (works in multiple languages).
title: Meme Generator and Template Database

api_list.name: /template/{image}
api_list.description:
The image path parameter corresponds to a meme template you want to add text too. Images are fixed width of 500px and variable length depending on the template for a list all available images call **/templates**  included in the responses is the number of available text boxes.
**template/:image** comes with predefined text boxes that are generally used with those images, text size is not included in the text box definitions.
If the text is larger then the box it will ignore the height restriction.
The request includes text0 <-> text**n** keys where **n** is the number of text boxes a meme template usually has, its not required to use all of them.
text**n** fields:
- text -> Text contents
- font -> What font to use
- font_size -> font size
- text_angle -> how many degrees to rotate the text box, the axis is the center of the text box
- text_color -> color of the text in (R,G,B) format that has to be a string exactly defines as examples 
- text\_stroke\_color -> text outline color (R,G,B)
- text\_stroke\_width -> width of the text outline
- text_align -> alignment of text inside of a text box can be 'center', 'left' or 'right'
- text_placement -> text placement inside of a text box can be 'center', 'top' or 'bottom'
- text_wrap -> Whether to wrap text to a new line if it goes over text box width either True or False
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://meme-generator-and-template-database.p.rapidapi.com/template/{image}"

headers = {
    "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
    "X-RapidAPI-Host": "meme-generator-and-template-database.p.rapidapi.com"
}

response = requests.post(url, headers=headers)

print(response.json())

api_list.name: /text-box/{image}
api_list.description:
The image path parameter corresponds to a meme template you want to add text too. Images are fixed width of 500px and variable length depending on the template for a list all available images call **/templates**.
**text-box/:image** requires the text boxes to be defined when sending the request (max 15 text boxes) sample structure provided in example.
If the text overflows the bounds of a text box it ignores the height parameter.
Text is always placed in the center of a text box and centered if it has multiple lines. 
Text Box Fields:

- x , y -> Where the left top corner of a text box is located on a image.
- width -> Width of a text box
- height -> Height of a text box (optional)
- text -> Text contents
- font -> What font to use
- font_size -> font size
- text_angle -> how many degrees to rotate the text box, the axis is the center of the text box
- text_color -> color of the text in (R,G,B) format that has to be a string exactly defines as examples 
- text\_stroke\_color -> text outline color (R,G,B)
- text\_stroke\_width -> width of the text outline
- text_align -> alignment of text inside of a text box can be 'center', 'left' or 'right'
- text_placement -> text placement inside of a text box can be 'center', 'top' or 'bottom'
- text_wrap -> Whether to wrap text to a new line if it goes over text box width either True or False
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://meme-generator-and-template-database.p.rapidapi.com/text-box/{image}"

headers = {
    "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
    "X-RapidAPI-Host": "meme-generator-and-template-database.p.rapidapi.com"
}

response = requests.post(url, headers=headers)

print(response.json())

api_list.name: /search
api_list.description: Returns meme templates that contain a specific string. **searchString is case sensitive**

api_list.name: /caption/{image}
api_list.description:
The image path parameter corresponds to a meme template you want to add text too.  Images are fixed width of 500px and variable length depending on the template, for a list of all available images call **/templates**.
**caption/:image** expands the image with the text added on the bottom or top depending  parameters the amount expanded is proportional to text height.
Request body (either for top/bot):

- text -> Text for the  caption
- font_size -> Font size for top text
- font -> What font to use
- text_color -> color of the text in "(R.G.B)"
- text_stroke_color -> text outline color "(R.G.B)"
- text_stroke_width -> width of the outline
- text_align -> alignment of text inside the caption can be either 'center', 'left' or 'right'

optional_parameters.name: top
optional_parameters.default: Thanks for trying out this meme generator

optional_parameters.name: bottom
optional_parameters.default: There is also a useless bottom caption that you can go without

api_list.name: /fonts
api_list.description:
Any of the fonts can be used  in any text box or caption.
Some fonts are language specific:
- Chinese -> zcool-wenyi
- Japanese -> takaopmincho
-  Korean -> gugi
- Hindi -> poppins
